 seal it ourselves)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;not cost-prohibitive (there are lots of places that have nice lights but even for a DIY solution, it's either 2 overpriced half-metres or the next level up is buying 5m which is way too much)...$40 plus shipping would be nice.  I guess we could spend up to $80 after shipping but really...we're replacing dollar-store lights here.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I came so close to finding something, but the few options that fit all criteria were made by companies that did not ship to Canada (thanks for telling me only once I reached the checkout, and not allowing this as a search criterion even when logged in, Amazon...)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There's also the one product &quot;exclusively licensed to Chariot&quot;, StrideLite:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://i.stack.imgur.com/FNdMJ.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;StrideLite system for Chariot&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;...but &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.buzzillions.com/reviews/chariot-carriers-inc-stridelite-strobe-kit-reviews?prRpp=10#bz-model-review-tabs-list&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;apparently it's terrible&lt;/a&gt;, which you can pretty much tell just by looking at it.  It doesn't light up the back at all, which is often the part you'll need to make more visible.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Any suggestions?  This is getting frustrating, and I'm surprised at the lack of solid options I've come across so far.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;" OwnerUserId="1037" LastEditorUserId="1037" LastEditDate="2011-02-15T19:07:30.320" LastActivityDate="2011-02-15T19:48:58.697" Title="Where to find a good bicycle-trailer lighting system...in Canada" Tags="&lt;regional&gt;&lt;trailer&gt;&lt;canada&gt;&lt;led-lights&gt;" AnswerCount="2" CommentCount="6" />
