ng to unfreeze them. &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Question:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is getting really old, so my question is: &lt;strong&gt;without obsessively cleaning them 1-2 times a day, how do I keep my disc brakes from getting gummed up?&lt;/strong&gt; If the answer is &quot;buy better disc brakes&quot;, that's fine. I just have no idea what to look for. &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;" OwnerUserId="3538" LastActivityDate="2013-02-06T15:45:01.910" Title="How to prevent my disc brakes from locking/sticking due to debris?" Tags="&lt;brakes&gt;&lt;winter&gt;&lt;disc-brake&gt;" AnswerCount="2" CommentCount="3" />
